                    <h2>Advanced Video Analytics</h2>
                    <p class="tech-text">Advanced Video Analytics is a critical feature in security surveillance systems that involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning algorithms to analyze video footage in real-time. This feature goes beyond traditional video monitoring by detecting and identifying specific objects, behaviors, or anomalies. By leveraging advanced video analytics, security systems can automatically alert operators to potential threats, intrusions, or unusual activities, enhancing the overall effectiveness of surveillance.</p>

                </section>
                <section id="service2" class="service__main-section">
                    <h2>High-Resolution Cameras</h2>
                    <p class="tech-text">High-Resolution Cameras form the foundation of clear and detailed surveillance. This feature involves using cameras with high resolution to capture crisp and detailed images and videos. High-resolution cameras not only provide accurate and reliable evidence in case of incidents but also enhance the ability to identify individuals and objects. The clarity offered by high-resolution cameras is essential for maximizing the surveillance system's monitoring capabilities.</p>

                </section>
                <section id="service3" class="service__main-section">
                    <h2>Facial Recognition Technology</h2>
                    <p class="tech-text">Facial Recognition Technology is a sophisticated feature that enables security surveillance systems to identify and verify individuals based on their facial features. This involves comparing facial patterns against a database of known faces. By incorporating facial recognition technology, security systems can enhance access control, track the movement of specific individuals, and improve overall security by quickly identifying persons of interest.</p>

                </section>
                <section id="service4" class="service__main-section">
                    <h2>Smart Intrusion Detection</h2>
                    <p class="tech-text">Smart Intrusion Detection is a feature that utilizes sensors, cameras, and analytics to identify unauthorized access or suspicious activities in secured areas. This involves setting up virtual perimeters or zones and triggering alerts when any unauthorized intrusion is detected. Smart intrusion detection not only improves response times but also minimizes false alarms by distinguishing between normal activities and potential security threats.</p>

                </section>
